node.text:
-
CHOC CARAMEL OXYWHEY😱🍫🎉
-
I am SO excited to finally announce my very own protein flavour in collaboration with @ehplabs. You all know that I’ve been using Oxywhey for years now and it has been my ULTIMATE compliance buddy throughout every stage of my fitness journey, since the very beginning 😍.
-
From hitting my sweet tooth during WBFF World Championships preparation when living the calorie deficit life, to fuelling my booty gains when in a surplus🍑... To have my own flavour is an absolute dream come true💫!
-
What I’ve learned over the years is that the key to success on your health and fitness journey is to be prepared and not to deprive. Having Oxywhey has allowed me to stay complaint to my goals while not missing out on living my best life (hellooo, protein oats every morning!). Oxywhey has:
-
💫25g protein per serve.
💫Super probiotics (gut health, hair & skin).
💫B Vitamins (vitality and energy).
💫Alkalising vitamins and minerals for optimal health.
💫100% pure, lean, non-GMO whey protein.
💫All flavours are 100% natural.
-
Head to the LINK IN MY BIO to sign up to the exclusive mailing list to be the first to know when you can get your hands on my EHP CHOC CARAMEL Oxywhey 😋🍫
-

Changing it up from fitness to fashion to give you girls the chance to win ALL my outfits in this video! All my favs 😍
-
To enter:
-
1️⃣LIKE this post.
2️⃣TAG your friends! The more tags the more chances to win!
3️⃣FOLLOW @laurensimpson & @babyboofashion .
-
Bonus points if you share this post to your story!! 💖
-
Competition ends Sunday! Winner selected at random & announced on IG stories. GOOD LUCK!🙏🏼

LOWER BODY HOME WORKOUT 🔥BIKINI X STRONG CHALLENGE SAMPLE! 👙💪🏼

Who is going to be doing the challenge from HOME??! Let me know….I am!🙋🏼‍♀️

Link in my bio to join @laurensimpson

The challenge has 2 training level options:
🔥Beginner/intermediate
🔥Advanced

**You can swap anytime between the programs in the app. You get access to ALL programs when you join. 👏🏼👏🏼

🔥ADVANCED ‘TRAIN LIKE LOZ’
5-6 days per week. Lower / Upper body split. 
I have designed this program around how I train from home. I have included so many new exercises/variations to lift the intensity of your home workouts. SAVAGE! 🙊

✨HOME TRAINING EQUIPMENT: dumbbells + booty band.

WORKOUT:

A1) SINGLE LEG HIP THRUST (double elevation to increase range of motion)
A2) DEFICIT REVERSE LUNGE
A3) DB LYING LEG PAUSE (pause in the bottom range)

B1) B-STANCE RDL
B2) FRONT RACK BULGARIAN (narrow stride)

Dropset:
C1) HEELS ELEVATED DB HACK SQUAT
C2) HEELS ELEVATED BODY WEIGHT HACK SQUAT

D) SQUAT JUMP AMRAP 🔥🔥🔥 if you don’t like jumping or can’t due to injury you can easily swap out a higher impact exercise like this in the app to something more suitable. 📲

My next challenge intake is now open for sign ups.
BIKINI X STRONG! Our most popular challenge is back!!! 🥳🥳🥳🥳

Link in my bio to secure your spot @laurensimpson

node.text:
LOW CALORIE SWEET SNACK OPTIONS: ALDI EDITION 🍭🍩✨

Here are a few foodie finds at Aldi that are approx 100 calories & under. I’ve also included some drink options too!

Now don’t come at me about lack of nutritional value or sUgAr 🙃. Im not saying this should form the basis of your diet - they are just a few fun snack options...and besides everything in moderation! You do not have to completely cut sugar! ✌🏼

My next 8 week challenge intake starts 16 Aug. Sign up NOW to gain instant access to the LSF APP 📲

Link in bio @laurensimpson

node.text:
⌛️WANT THAT SNATCHED WAIST?

Ditch the waist trainer. 🙅🏼‍♀️Save your money girls.

When I was a bikini competitor, a key area to work on was building width of the upper body (lats/delts) to give you that tapered down look.

I don’t genetically have a tiny waist (I’m very straight up and down) but one of the best things about weight training is that you can build muscle and really shape your body!

A nice wide back and shoulders gives you the illusion of a smaller waist! ⌛️

So NO you do not have to wear a waist trainer to get a small waist -
 🙅🏼‍♀️🙅🏼‍♀️🙅🏼‍♀️If you want a smaller waist:

1. LOSE FAT. Lowering body fat will also help enhance your waist to back ratios.
2. Build your upper body (back and shoulders to create width) and also your legs (glutes, quads, hamstrings).

Build muscle to create that shape! 👏🏼👏🏼

BACK & DELTS WORKOUT:
Lat pulldown 3X 10
Pull ups 3X max reps
Lateral raise 3x 12
Rear delt cable row 3x 15

ENJOY!💪🏼
LSF TEAM STRONG GIRLS

node.text:
I used to be insecure about my scars. Growing up I used to wear one piece swimwear so none of the other kids could see I was different. 🥺

This week I received quite a few messages thanking me for normalising scars, for posting photos for my newest challenge campaign without my scars being photoshopped out.❤️🙏🏼

What are my scars from?

To quickly fill any of my new followers in - my horizontal scar of my tummy is from a kidney cancer I had when I was young. It’s faded so so much over the years. The newest vertical scar is from February 2020 when I had an emergency surgery for a twisted bowel. (Looks like a + sign 🙊 )

My message to you today:

Don’t be ashamed of the scars life has left with you. They are reminders of your victory - you survived. They are a sign of strength.

This goes for stretch marks, cellulite, blemishes, those lil lumps and bumps, and any marks on your body for that matter.

PERFECTION DOES NOT EXIST. We are human. Our bodies are marked. These are signs of experience and LIFE. 🌸🙏🏼

It may push you beyond your comfort zone but learn to embrace your scars, your curves, your marks…everything about you that makes you uniquely YOU.

So go on rock your favourite bikini & own it.

YOU ARE DIFFERENT - that is your super power. 💗⚡️

Work on your confidence, lift like a boss & eat like a queen in my next 8 week challenge BIKINI X STRONG. Join me and thousands of women worldwide.🌍👯‍♀️

Sign up now via link in my bio @laurensimpson

FIX YOUR FORM: CABLE CRUNCHES ✅❌ 

This is one of my favourite weighted abs exercises. It’s one you all commonly ask me about so I hope this post is helpful to break it down.

I am a COACH so I want to help you with as many little tips and tricks to perfect your form in the gym! Getting your technique on point in the gym will go a long way in getting you the results you deserve!

My key do’s & don’ts! 

🔥Keep your hips locked down. You don’t need to move your butt up and down as you crunch. Keep your lower body fixed. Moving your hips is creating momentum and you are using other muscles to then pull the rope down - we don’t want this.

🔥The movement should come from your spine. The goal is spinal flexion. As @coachmarkcarroll says ‘roll up your spine’. That cue has stuck with me. You should first initiate the movement with your lower abs tucking under and then rolling your spine from there - kinda like a ‘double crunch’. I try get my elbows to my knees. On the way back up get to a full stretch (while keeping your lower body fixed) and then crunch back down. Imagine bringing down your chest and rolling it up to your belly button. 

🔥Keep your chin tucked and hands and arms fixed. Again, you don’t want to be using your arms to pull down the rope. You want to isolate your core.

🔥Focus on getting a deep SQUEEZE with your ab muscles. Breathe out while rolling up for a deeper contraction of your abs!!! 🔑

🔥Keep it controlled. No points for getting through the reps fastest - remember that!!

I hope this video helped!♥️💪🏼

node.text:
ME THEN VS ME NOW

2015: Even though I look lean - this is what you don’t see👇🏼

🚫Severely under eating. Basically starving myself of nutrients my body needed to thrive. I went through vigorous cycles of extreme calorie restriction and then binging.
🚫 Avoided social outings because I couldn’t track my food properly.
🚫I exercised purely to burn calories. I only wanted to do cardio at the beginning because I was scared of the weights room.
🚫I was the least confident in myself I had even been in my life - despite being at my lowest weight. I was so insecure.
🚫I felt like I was never good enough. 

2021: NOW...

🦋I eat to fuel my body & have developed a healthy relationship with food.
🦋I lift HEAVY AF and want to be strong.
🦋I am more confident in myself, and know my value and worth.
🦋I am in control of my life & happiness. I don’t let fear of judgement from others keep me from reaching my full potential.
🦋I am educated, but I am also continuously learning, growing & evolving. 
🦋I wake up excited for every day.

My progress is a result of years of consistency and hard work. It’s never perfect - but I keep going. I don’t give up.🔥

You have the power to step into the GIRL you are designed to be. The power is in your hands… you just have to decide you truly want it. 💪🏼

Let me coach you.

BIKINI X STRONG 8 week CHALLENGE is here! 🥳🥳
The ultimate transformation challenge for your body + mindset.

Sign up now & get access to the LSF APP!

LINK IN MY BIO @laurensimpson

node.text:
BIKINI X STRONG 💜💪🏼8 WEEK CHALLENGE 😱 Our most iconic challenge is BACK..BIGGER & BETTER!💥
Link in my bio to join now @laurensimpson

This challenge encompasses everything I am about as a person, coach & brand.

✨STRONG CONFIDENT FEMALES. 👑✨

This is THE challenge to give you the full experience to train exactly like me. I’m giving you the secrets of a World Bikini Champion with your food, training & mindset to get your own TRANSFORMATION.✨

There is so much NEW for this challenge!!!🤩

💪🏼8 week training programs. 2 experience level options for our GYM and HOME programs - Beginner/ Intermediate + ‘TRAIN LIKE LOZ’ Advanced.

➡️Beginner/Intermediate: 4 days per week (2 optional days) Workouts approx 45 minutes. Gain confidence with your training & watch how fast you will progress!

➡️’TRAIN LIKE LOZ’ Advanced: 5 days per week (6th optional day)
1 hour workouts + advanced finishers.
Focus on getting stronger on the main lifts!
Both home + gym programs are based off my own EXACT training.

So many new exercises & variations added to these challenges programs. LEVEL UP 💪🏼

🍎You will get a custom meal plan + macros/calories. 50+ new meals added to the extensive database (750+), New recipes added + brand new cooking videos added to the LSF app weekly!!!!👏🏼👏🏼

🥳‘PRE-SEASON’ CHALLENGE PROGRAM!! BRAND NEW for LSF! Sign up now and get immediate access to the LSF APP! We are prepping you in advance. You will have a bonus program to start now in the lead up!!

📲 BRAND NEW APP DESIGN! Sleek new look and feel. Loving the new vibe for your home for the next 8 weeks. ✨ 

🔥I’ve been able to team up with EHPLABS again to offer you HUGE bundle savings with supplements + challenge!

The challenge also includes all the other incredible benefits such as our exclusive Facebook community, live chats with me, educational videos content, check ins + MORE.

Official start: 16 August.
⁠
💜Become the strongest, sexiest most confident version of yourself 💫. It’s time to build YOUR best bikini body 🔥

SIGN UPS NOW OPEN 🗓. LINK IN BIO to secure your spot👏🏼👏🏼👏🏼 @laurensimpson 

SO WHO’S IN? TAG YOUR GIRLS!

ANY QUESTIONS? Drop them below

FIX YOUR FORM: PUSH UPS ❌✅

PLEASE SAVE + RE-SHARE 🙏🏼🙏🏼

Push ups are a VERY common exercise. Its  body weight only and can be done in some variation regardless of your fitness experience level.

As a coach, I do see a lot of people struggle with them…and a lot of the time I think it’s because they aren’t actually sure what a proper push up should look like!

Here are some common issues and then how it’s corrected.

COMMON MISTAKES

❌HEAD LEADING THE MOVEMENT
❌HANDS TOO FAR FORWARD. When you are in position they should be directly under your shoulders.
❌HIPS TOO HIGH/TOO LOW. This puts unnecessary strain on your lower back. You aren’t using your core here to stabilise your body.
❌HANDS TOO WIDE. This limits your range of motion.
❌ELBOWS FLARED. Elbows should not be pointing directly out to the sides. This is putting strain on your shoulders and not putting your chest in proper alignment to work the muscles you want to be!

FORM TIPS:

✅ELBOWS TUCKED IN SLIGHTLY - AT A 45 DEGREE ANGLE
✅HINGE FROM KNEES (NOT HIPS)
✅HANDS SLIGHTLY WIDER THAN SHOULDER-WIDTH APART.
✅HEAD IN LINE WITH BODY. Maintain alignment with your spine.
✅CORE ENGAGED
✅HIPS DOWN

From a kneeling push up - you can progress to doing them up on your toes.🏆

How many can you do?

I hope this was helpful. ❤️ LET ME KNOW! 🙏🏼

P.s. 1 day to go until the next 8 week challenge will be announced! 🥳

node.text:
GYM HACK: NO BACK EXTENSION MACHINE? TRY THIS!💡💥🤯

I’ve posted this set up hack previously but it was the first time for me doing it at home so thought I’d film and share again!! 👏🏼

Back extensions are one of my favourite for glutes! If your gym doesn’t have the machine try this simple set up using a squat rack, plates & bar pad.

The plates behind your feet will ensure you don’t slip. The pad on the bar will help cushion your hips.

Tip: when doing back extension focus on driving your hips back as you lower down. Initiate the movement from your hips and push your butt back. You should feel this deep in your glute-ham tie in area.

Please let me know if this hack was helpful! ❤️

P.s. 1 day to go until the next 8 week challenge intake is announced 🥳🥳
@laurensimpsonfitness
